     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="8"/>
   <head>Ad Authorem.</head>
   <l>HE that shall read thy chara<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>cters <hi>(Nic: Breton)</hi>
   </l>
   <l>And weigh them well; must say they are well written.</l>
   <l>They taste the lampe: much rea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ding, obseruation,</l>
   <l>Art, matter, wit, all worthy com<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>mendation.</l>
   <l>Some weaue their lines of such a slender thred,</l>
   <l>They will not last so long, as to be read.</l>
   <l>Thou hast so spunne, so weau'd; thy words, thy lines</l>
   <l>They please vs most being viewd, a hundred times.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>W.D.</signed>
   </closer>
